  <m>{\color{magenta}\text{To convert temperature from Kelvin to Degrees celsius, subtract 273 from the temperature in Kelvin.} }</m>
</p>
<example>
  <statement>
    <p>
      Convert 472 Kelvin to degree Celsius.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      <md>
        <mrow>^\circ C = \amp K - 273  , where K is 472 in our question.</mrow> 
        <mrow> = \amp (472 - 273)^\circ C</mrow>
        <mrow> 472K = \amp 199 ^\circ C </mrow>
      </md>
    </p>
    <p>
      The temperature in degrees celsius is <m>{\color{magenta}199 ^\circ C}</m>
    </p>
  </solution>
</example>
<example>
  <statement>
    <p>
      The temperature of Tana River town was <m>292\text{K}</m> on Saturday .What was the temperature in degrees Celsius?
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      <md>
        <mrow>^\circ C = \amp K - 273  , where K is 292 in our question.</mrow> 
        <mrow> = \amp (292 - 273)^\circ C</mrow>
        <mrow> 292K = \amp 19 ^\circ C </mrow>
      </md>
    </p>
    <p>The temperature of Tana River was <m>{\color{magenta}19 ^\circ C}</m></p>
  </solution>
</example>
